  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Young patients with rheumatic diseases have challenges different from older patients due to
      their life situation. It has been reported that they do not have the same benefit from age
      non-specific rehabilitation in warm climate. This trial will test the effect of a specially
      adapted version of a rehabilitation program delivered in Spain (warm climate) for Norwegian
      young adults aged 20-35 years.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
